@gabbyscheyen Kay a lot of people ask me what exercises they can do to get rid of lower back fat... y'all you can't train away fat. There are no movements that help you lose back fat specifically. LOSING FAT COMES FROM A CALORIE DEFICIT. Aka, less calories then your body needs to function. You can achieve a deficit by burning extra calories through weight training, HIIT/LISS, or you can eat less calories to maintain a deficit. You can't just do an exercise and expect to lose fat from that area on your body... YOU👏🏼CAN'T👏🏼TARGET👏🏼FAT LOSS. You have to lose fat ALL OVER your body in order to lose "love handles". And I'm sorry to say but depending on genetics it may be hard for you to achieve that in a healthy way. We all genetically lose fat in different areas and at different rates. As women, we are BUILT to hold fat around our midsections. I hold fat in my back too. When I wear tight low rise pants you BET my fat hangs over (which is why I only wear high waisted leggings). But I pose in ways that makes me look best. I know my good angles in photos. Bottom line, you can't just train legs to lose fat on your thighs and you can't just train arms to lose fat on your arms. So you cant do back workouts to lose just fat on your back. You have to lose fat everywhere through a calorie deficit. "British Columbia’s representative for children and youth says indigenous kids are being removed from their homes and placed in care because agencies supporting their families are underfunded.  Bernard Richard blames both the provincial and federal governments, saying current funding models mean aboriginal agencies are unlikely to provide the same level of help compared with their non-aboriginal counterparts.  Richard says in a report that the province’s confusing funding arrangements with agencies delegated to help aboriginal families mean inequitable services depending on where indigenous children live.  He says the Canadian Human Rights Tribunal’s finding last year of discriminatory funding for aboriginal child welfare has also not led to action by the federal government.  Richard’s report says aboriginal agencies are struggling to cover operational costs and can’t pay equal wages compared with those offered by the province to employees in the Children’s Ministry.  Children’s Minister Stephanie Cadieux released a statement saying Richard’s conclusions don’t reflect many of the recent improvements the province has made to help ensure better outcomes for indigenous children and families.  Richard’s report is based on interviews with 45 staff in the aboriginal agencies, including child-protection workers, and an international review of staffing issues involving indigenous child-welfare systems." #firstnations #decolonize #wayoflife #childhood #children #wellbeing #wellness #health #canada150 #government #governmentofcanada #britishcolumbia #vancouver #vancity #penticton #kelowna #awareness #genocide #ontario #toronto #halifax #edmonton #calgary #winnipeg #brokenpromises #doublestandards #racism #humanrights #water #family

A heartfelt & emotional throwback. This young man, at only 34, changed the entire direction of my life. Talk about impact and purpose. My late uncle Brian wasn't even a singer but was very educated and passionate when it came to opera. While he was alive it was his mission to instil his passion for opera in me. I casually sang some silly little song for him one day and he jumped up and said: Honey, you have a voice made for opera! Thus began the seasons tickets at the COC, buying me vocal scores, having me sing at his lavish parties, even emotionally coaching me on how to portray 'the tears in your voice, Tonia.' (Maria Callas was our go-to as the perfect example.) To quote him when I was a young singer, 'Tonia, you will hit your prime in your 40's. This is when you will come into your own.' And my god was he ever right. There's something about being in my 40's, things are unlocking and unfolding. You can't rush a fine wine, and you certainly can't rush the twists, turns, and detours of your life's journey because it is ALL part of what makes you, you, and contributes to your destiny. I am grateful for all of it. I got so present to this today in a coaching with Caren Levine who coaches between here in Miami and the MET opera, a rush! And knowing how much my uncle Brian LOVED to dance, I just know that he would be grooving to the new music I've found myself writing. Brian, you're with me, STILL, and I'll never stop working the gift God gave me and the desire you placed in my heart! 🙏🏻❤️ #throwback #throwbackthursday #singer #songwriter #mentor #influence #anartistsjourney #blessed #uncle #opera #passion #toronto #torontolife #performer #wishescometrue #40  #femaledj #dj #mariacallas #coc #carenlevine #mannyparez #miami #musiciansofinstagram #photo #gifts #purpose #mastinkipp @mastinkipp #thedailylove #growingintograce

@janeseymourfonda  Jane is starring along side her pal Lilly Tomlin in the @netflix hit tv series @graceandfrankie  Jane Fonda 268 is a screen print by Andy Warhol from 1982  This photograph is a reflection of me looking at this screen print in the pop up gallery "Andy Warhol Revisited: A Pop Art Exhibit" by @revolvergallery in Toronto Dec 2015  @iloveandywarhol is a major sponsor of this fabulous Andy Warhol touring exhibit  I've done a series of these "Reflections of Andy's Jane Fonda 268" like I'd done with the "Marilyn Reflections"  Each photo and edit has a different style..vibe .. I'll post more of of these in the next few weeks  So I've edited this per usual .. I wanted to give it a 21st Century edgy design vibe  It's now black and white as well as with many different filters  and I'm reflected in it ... as well as the iconic Campbell Soup Cans screen prints and an art visitor in the gallery  I'm a lifelong admirer of Jane Fonda .. she just keeps getting better and better ...and so does Lilly Tomlin!  @janeseymourfonda #janefonda #actress #icon #comedian #comedy @graceandfrankie #graceandfrankie #tvseries #andywarhol #screenprint #janefonda268 #portrait #woman #beautiful #photographer #penelwoods #digitalartist #creativedirector #bw #blackandwhite #vsco #contemporaryart #popart @revolvergallery #eighties #fashion #fashionover40 @iloveandywarhol #design #andywarholrevisitedtorontogallery #the6ix #toronto #instagram

If you're going through hard shit right now, keep going! . . The human body, mind and spirit is so adaptive that it can grow and strengthen to ANY stimuli imposed upon it, and also weaken when nothing is imposed upon it. We grow when we're challenged, we grow when we're broken down, we grow when we're faced with obstacle, adversity, stress and pain. . . Your mind is no different than your muscles or bones, when it's challenged with an external force, it strengthens in order to meet that demand placed upon it. It is for that same reason that astronauts come back to earth with a lesser bone density because their bones aren't used in outer space to the degree that they are on earth due to the gravitational pull. In fact, it takes them 3-years to regain that same bone density.  We adapt to our environment, stress and challenge, or lack thereof. . . If you're faced with pain or challenge, embrace it because it's THAT pain or challenge that's the precursor and catalyst in making you one strong motherfucker. You may not realize it now, but when you look back at your life you'll realize that it was THAT event that caused you to grow, and if you're ever faced with that pain again it wouldn't inflict pain upon you. The key to growth is to never surrender to your circumstances no matter how bad they get, pain doesn't come to stay it comes to pass. Be thankful for the people and things that have hurt you, they're a blessing in disguise. @themindbuilder

This happens every year when a regular season team is doing good and people start saying they could challenge Lebron but still lose. It happened with the Nets, Pacers, Raptors, and every team! This is because Lebron doesn't care for no regular season! It means nothing at all as he will make the playoffs and go to finals. The best chances are for Toronto and Washington who will most likely win 2 games max. I was tagged in this last night by the amazing Darla from @theartofrearranging (give her a follow you won't be disappointed) - I usually don't play along with these but this ones kinda fun so here goes !! 1- I am 28 year old mother to 3 boys 2- my husband is from Mexico and 50% of the time at home I talk with a fake Spanish accent. I can't help it 3- I'd like to have one more child before I'm 30😬 4- we have horses but I've never had a chance to learn to ride properly because I've always been pregnant 5- I am a total goof most of the time with a ridiculous sense of humour 6- I love music. It's one of the ways my soul speaks 7- I play guitar and piano but I'm a bit rusty  8- I'm very shy and uncomfortable in big groups 9- I prefer to keep my opinions to myself because ... well let's just leave it at that ;) 10- my mom is one of my best friends and favourite people to hang out with  11- when I still lived at home me and my dad had a best out of 101 games of cribbage over a few weeks - he won but it was close 12- I love being outside nature is my favourite 13- I love reading cheesy novels  14- I love watching cheesy movies  15- taking a bath is like a mini vacation for me and I do it often 16- aside from facebook and instagram I am not friends with anyone I went to school with ever 17- aside from my best friend that I met in grade 5 but she's basically just a sister  18- speaking of sisters I have 2 sisters and 2 brothers - second youngest out of 5  19- I love cooking and trying new recipes but my entire family is picky so I don't get to do it often 20- I adore being a stay at home mom in the traditional sense (don't get me wrong I totally respect working moms and major kudos to single moms out there killing it)  Wow if you read that thanks for reading!! It's hard to talk that much about yourself hahaha let's see who else wants to play? @sacred_cinder @mvanmaanen.designs @mysweetrelish @minspiredliving I dunno I don't have any friends haha. Have fun with it it's neat getting to know each other !! #20questions #thisisme #justalilbit

This year’s #TorontoCarnival celebrates 50 years of music, #costumes, and #culture and bringing creativity to the streets of #Toronto. . The DFZ invites those interested to participate in a one day 💥hack-a-thon💥 that will challenge participants to leverage advanced #digitaldesign and #fabrication methods to create an 💥innovative #carnivalcostume💥. Using the theme of ‘Chrysalis’, hack-a-thon participants will organize into small teams to #design, digitally model and prototype a 💥#costumeconcept that is transformative💥. The winning team/costume concept will be awarded a cash prize of $500.00 and will be invited to collaborate with Nia on the development of their 💥2017 Toronto Caribbean Carnival Collection💥. . The DFZ has developed a series of experimental #digital and analog #techniques and related material systems to direct the #costumedesign workflow of the hack-a-thon. DFZ Mentors and technicians will be available to work with each group over the course of the day to develop the costume designs. . 💥REGISTER HERE: For hack-a-thon schedule and to register, please go to: http://tinyurl.com/organicismhackathon💥 . #WithPurpose #CarnivalArts

Hi everyone!  This is Louis-Bernard St-Jean (@LBStJean) again for Petroff Gallery's artist #takeover! To follow Instagram's #throwbackthursday tradition, and with so much water pouring from the sky today, I would like to showcase a piece about aquatic life I painted back in 2014, the artwork titled 'Corail' [Coral]. Of unsettling depth and movement, the vibrant colors of coral reefs mark this artwork, in which the viewer is pulled into this underwater world where the beauty of the marine ecosystem’s flora and fauna equals in fragility. Corail's painting style also presents a clear nod to one of my strongest art influences, Jean-Paul Riopelle's instantly recognizable palette knife works.  Many of my pieces from 2014-2015 are based on those techniques, as I was at the time studying and learning everything I could from them... And in parallel, also looking for any potentially working variations derived from these techniques that I could further develop and use profusely instead, experimenting on other pieces, seeing the results and evaluating their potential... which progressively led me to my own unique sculptural style!  The artwork Corail is currently on display in Petroff Gallery's front window, next to one of my most recent pieces, the artwork 'West Indies' (second photo)... Two paintings of the same size, made only three years apart!

@Regrann from @adam__rehab - 💬 We last talked about the Serratus Anterior and its ability to pull the #Scapula forward causing havoc with the Rhomboids. Though that area is always overlooked so to can a few other large muscles. 📔There are a few muscles that act directly on the humerus and cause rounded 🔄 shoulders or internal rotation in anatomical terms. 🤓 No one likes rounded shoulders...It's one of the 1⃣st things my clients notice about their posture.💪1⃣Latissimus Dorsi: This muscle runs from your TL fascia, pelvis and spine and travels upwards passing into the armpit to attach to the front and 🔝part of the humerus. Its action is to medially rotate, extend and adduct the humerus. Basically act like you are in cuffs 👮 and that's where this muscle puts your arms. 💪2⃣Teres Major: We call this Lats little helper 🚼 and it runs from the inferior angle of your scapula to the same place as the Lats does, and has the same action❗ 🏊 📕We can see in the pictures that these muscles are really large and could imagine they would be active during most of our daily activities. 🗯If you're only working on your Pecs and now Serratus Anterior to open your shoulders don't forget about these 2⃣ muscles that you can barely see from the front.  #rounded #shoulder #lats ##teres #pecs #posture #myodetox #toronto #knowledge #bomb #anatomy #massagetherapy #physio #learning #stretch #stretching - #regrann

YOUR TENSION HEADACHES MAY BE COMING FROM YOUR JAW! . For those of you that rarely get headaches unless you drink too much 🍺🍷, consider yourself lucky 🍀 . Headaches (HA) are the most common disorders of the nervous system. There are 4 main types of headache disorders . 🔹MIGRAINES are more often found in women, 2-1 ratio. They are recurring and tend to be one-sided and pulsing and can last a few hours to a few days 🔹CLUSTER (CH) are more common in men, 6-1 ratio and consist of a recurring (several times a day) brief but intense and extremely sever HA 🔹MEDICATION-OVERUSE HA are caused by excessive use of medication to treat HA (ironic, I know) and are often persistent and worst in the mornings 🔹TENSION TYPE HEADACHES (TTH) can last a few hours or more and can feel like pressure or tightness sometimes in the front, side or back of the head . TTH In my clinical experience are commonly caused by the TMJ muscles. It's  regular thing for people that have had a blow to the head, a fall, been in a car accident or have high levels of stress to suffer from TTH . You can do the sequence of external or internal jaw techniques in my last post or if you have a similar pattern in the 📸 use a tennis ball and lay on your side to knead out the trigger points. If you find a tender spot in the muscle, it may recreate your headache. This is okay and you should keep the ball on the "spot" until you feel it melt or the referral dissipate . . Cahneeval is like no other, its literally a week worth of partying and getting on wild and wotles! Each year hundreds of thousands of people gather on the small islands to celebrate 2 days of carnival and plenty of pre-carnival festivities such as J'ouvert which is the early morning celebration of carnival, before the actual carnival. Phytoglucol DeSlim memiliki fungsi utama sebagai Detox dan Slimming. Merupakan minuman yang terdiri dari 2 formulasi dengan kegunaan berbeda untuk tujuan yang sama.  Detox berfungsi untuk mempercepat proses pembuangan racun dalam tubuh.  Slimming berfungsi untuk melancarkan pencernaan dan BAB serta memperbaiki metabolisme tubuh.  Keduanya bukan hanya bertujuan untuk menurunkan berat badan, namun juga menjaga kestabilan berat badan secara alami.

Fasting is one of the most recommended acts during this spiritual season. It becomes Wajib during the month of Ramadan, but is highly recommended during the months of Rajab and Sha’baan. As will be noted from the Hadith above and others to follow, fasting, be it for only one day during these months, is rewarded with untold bounties.  Salmaan Farsi narrates that the Final messenger of Allah (SAW) said that there is a day in the month of Rajab on which if a person fasts and does Qiyaamul Lail (night vigil ) on that night, he will receive rewards like a person who fasts for 100 years and does Qiyaamul Lail for nights of 100 years. This night is the night of the 27th (Rajab) and the day of the 27th (Rajab). This is the day on which Hazrat Muhammad (SAW) was appointed to Messengerhood, (Ghuniyatut Talibeen, Tarteeb Shareef page 781) Imam Kazim(as) is reported to have said "Rajab is (the name of) a River in paradise that is whiter than milk & sweeter than honey. Allah will allow one to drink from this river if he fasts for even one day in this month.It is also a month of seeking forgiveness more than usual as Allah is forgiving & merciful during this month. . . . . . . . . . . . #الله_أكبر #الحمد_لله #محمد_صلى_الله_عليه_وسلم #امام_علی #حضرت_زهرا_سلام_الله_علیها #امام_حسن #امام_حسین #اسلام  #allah #muhammadﷺ #imamali #imamhassan #imamhusain #alhamdulillah #allahuakbar #islam #islamicsayings #islamicquotes #afghanyouthcommittee #toronto #canada #Iraq #kazemain #Karbala #Najaf #bainulharamain #jannatulbaqi #qom #mashhad #jamkaran

Something that many seem to have forgotten in choosing the right #realestate to invest in is that choosing the right #neighbourhood is as important as the right #home. With so many in #Toronto who have bought pre 2012 that are sitting on large amounts of equity, it's a good opportunity to sell the home and use some of that money to do it all over again. Many of the hot areas now were not on the radar in 2000. "Selling hot and buying cold" is a wonderful option if you can you want to take the money you've made and start fresh in a new area that is more in your price range. Do this a few times over a few decades and you'll have a nice nest egg to hatch. #torontorealestate #relocation #successplan

Mid way into your set and you see John explaining to his friends how to fit pizza 🍕 into a daily calorie intake will get abs. _  The faces I make while training is something else 😭but yeah don't eat that pre workout pizza. Sculpting a good physique isn't black and white but some of y'all make things too complicated with all these detoxing, IIFYM, fruit and water diet and other funny diets. The next time you step into the gym and find a lean person; ask him or her how long they've been training for; most of them would probably say 2-3 years. He/she most likely understands how some certain group of food affects their bodies. For a beginner, you've to understand the concept behind eating quality food to help build a lean structure. Yeah you can have a cheat meal 1-2 times a week depending on your goal but if you haven't gotten to your goals; why are you cheating? The moment you start eating pizza every other day; saying it's a "cheat meal" and you'll wonder why your aren't gaining results. Remember fuel your body with quality food to build an awesome body. Have a great weekend guys💪🏾. _  Need help figuring out your daily calorie intake to meet your goals? Send me a dm/ am email and I'll be glad to help you. #ThePhysique101

I'm not certain if it was the cause of my more-than-normal frizz but I digress.  It smells fantastic and goes on smooth... I don't think @Pantene gets enough love from us curly girls..but let me tell you something - through the "trying this new curl product" to another..this stuff has been my ish and my ultimate go to. They need to better advertise their curly hait stuff...its pretty good on my hair and it comes through time and time again! Day one curls may be a little crunchy but day 2 and day 3...whoooooo! My curls are just to die for! Try if if you haven't yet. Slouchy boots have been driving me nuts this week!!! I found a permanent way to keep them put using Velcro! You only need to make 1 pair of garter belt using thick elastic band. While full-body workouts seem to be increasing in popularity, body-part splits, most of which train a muscle group once a week, are still the predominate style of training for the vast majority of bodybuilders (~69%). [1] This is typically done using a 5-day body part split.  The following is research and reasons why higher training frequencies, in the form of full-body workouts and upper/lower splits, are superior for muscle and strength gains.  Studies that investigated the effects of training muscle groups between 1 to 3 days per week, on a volume-equated basis, showed higher frequencies of training were consistently superior to lower frequencies for increasing muscle mass. [2, 3]  Myofibrillar (muscle) protein synthesis (MPS, the process of muscle tissue growth and repair) last ~48 hours after resistance training [4] with other studies showing MPS levels returning to baseline after ~36 hours. [5] These levels also decrease as you advance as a lifter. [6] Note: There's one study that suggests MPS may not be correlated to hypertrophy [7] so let’s make this a tentative point.  A meta-analysis found 2–3 sets resulted in 46% greater gains in hypertrophy than 1 set, where 4–6 sets only resulted in 13% greater gains than 2–3 sets. [8] As you can see, there are diminishing returns as you continue to do more sets on the same muscle group in a single session.  Greater overall muscle activation from full-body training enables your body is better utilize larger doses of post-workout dietary protein which further stimulate MPS. [9]  You can certainly​ make great progress training muscle groups once a week.  But remember, it's not about what works, it's about works best.  References:  1. https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/22990567  2. https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/27102172  3. https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25932981  4. https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9252485  5. https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/8563679  6. https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9886957  7. http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0089431  8. https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20300012  9. https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/27511985

I believe that our understanding of precious time is displayed through our desire to take photos. Looking through photographs we took yesterday, or years ago makes us thoughtful. It takes us back to the moment it was taken - what we were thinking, how we were feeling, who was beside us. People shouldn't be judged when they want to take a picture of places they go, food they eat or friends they're with. It's our modern instinct. We should see it as a privilege that we have the resources to immortalize the moments we choose.

Back in 2010 I was managing a #footlocker when these shoes came out. I had first dibs at all releases, so there was no way I was going to pass these up. So on release day I had these put aside to buy them after my shift. During the day these were selling out quickly, we only had a size run. A guy came in with a desperate look on his face and his fingers crossed hoping we still had his size left. Unfortunately we did not. He told me he needed these and they were very special for him since it was the first Jordan is late mom bought him. That pulled at my heart strings, I went to stockroom and resurfaced with my pair for him to buy. He could not believe it he was so thrilled. Fast forward 7 years and karma came around full circle as a guy I do trades with gifted me these for the best steal I ever got. He told me he had many offers but knew how badly I wanted these, he took a loss to help me out. He's a young collector so he gives me hope that there's still passion, honour and respect in the game. #fouronekix

Grossman's Tavern has been "home of the blues" in Toronto for six decades. Grossman's opened as a cafeteria in 1948 and got a liquor licence a few years later. Over the years blues, R&B and jazz has mixed with the dive bar ambience. It's said that Dan Aykroyd would jam on his harmonica here in the '70s and often came to see the Downchild Blues Band, which was one of his inspirations for the Blues Brothers. Paul Shaffer played here years before his Letterman gig. Mondays are jam night and Grossman's boasts it never charges a cover to get in. A great Toronto live music venue whose worn sign is probably an apt reflection of its clientele.

Excelente ejercicio para potenciar musculatura glútea 👆 #Repost @dr.alexritza with @repostapp ・・・ Dr Alex’s Sitting Antidote 💊  Part 2️⃣5️⃣ SUPER SPY GLUTE STRENGTHENER for the office🏢  This is the James Bond and Carrie Mathison of strengthening exercises because it is some super spy stuff.  In a world where we do everything in front of us with little side-to-side movement, the gluteus medius and minimis muscles that stabilize the pelvis and hip are vastly underused and usually weak. Weakness in these glutes is a HUGE contributor to hip problems, back pain and the cause of most running injuries in my experience.  In short, strengthening these lateral stabilizers is so important so anyone living the #desklife especially if you are active outside of the office. This exercise is fantastic because it is effective and can be done inconspicuously at the office while you work!  STEP 1: Sit or stand with exceptional posture as discussed previously STEP 2: Loop a Theraband around the knees, shin, ankle or forefoot STEP 3: Brace your core Step 4: Using the glutes on the side of your hips, draw the feet and knees apart from each other without allowing any sideways bending at the knee STEP 5: Hold for 60 seconds or as long as possible STEP 6: Repeat for 3 or more sets STEP 7: Progress this exercise by placing the resistance band father and farther towards the toes. IMPORTANT – For knee safety, do not progress the looping of the Theraband close to the toes unless you can maintain a straight angle between the hips, knees and ankles. FITS Hold for 10-60 seconds. Repeat for strengthening purposes for 3 sets of 10-60 seconds two times daily.  #fisioterapia #gluteos #toronto #chiropractic #physiotherapy #physio #massage #crossfit #health #wellness #nutrition #theSix #the6 #strong #chiro #spine #gains #posture #rehab

BODYWORK PROGRESSION❗️ SWIPE LEFT ⬅️ . . Here's a great example of what the body can do with space and time! 👏🏼The photo on the LEFT and photo on the RIGHT are 7 MONTHS APART! 📆 . . ☑️The LEFT photo was taken before session 1 of the KMI-Series. ☑️The MIDDLE photo was taken after session 12 of the KMI-Series. ☑️The RIGHT photo was taken recently. . After completing the Structural Integration Series (roughly about 1 session per week for 12 weeks) and coming in for an occasional "tune-up" appointment to help the body integrate and further progress, in approx. 7 months we are looking at a very different body! I often say to clients that they may get taller throughout the series- literally! Given the opportunity, the body will continue to become more open and upright! 🆙 . . BODY READING NOTES: 👀 Due to the shortening of the DFL, the body had organized itself with bends, shifts and rotations... The before photo demonstrates a tilt in the pelvis (displayed well with the waistband), a lateral shift in the rib cage, a tilt in the shoulder girdle, and a rotation in the pelvis and shoulder girdle. . The far right photo demonstrates how the body has "unwound" after having time to settle with the continuous progression of work. . . . FINAL THINGS TO NOTE: This client originally was referred to me with chronic pain😣 in various places and was no longer able to be as active as he was previously. Now (after 7 months) this client exercises 3 TIMES A WEEK with various activities from running🏃🏻 to weight training🏋🏻 and experiences NO PAIN at all! . . It's amazing what the body is capable of given the care, commitment, and attention it deserves. . **i'm grateful for the kind permission to use these photos** . . . . . . . #buildingmachines #creatingspace #facilitatingchange #healing #anatomy #growing #evolving #body #muscles #tendons #toronto #eastend #rangeofmotion #performance #painfree #selfcare #structuralintegration #KMI #antomytrains

Enjoying Japan cherry blossom at Fushimi Momoyama Jyo (Castle), Kyoto. This is one of the most beautiful secret place to see and enjoy cherry blossom. Definitely no crowded and you surety will enjoy a wonderful serene moment here, because all the visitors here are local Japanese, almost no tourist will come to here. There are lots of cherry trees in different colors in this castle.  Fushimi Momoyamajyo is one of the eleven wards in the city of Kyoto, in Kyoto Prefecture, Japan. Fushimi Castle, originally built by Toyotomi Hideyoshi, with its rebuilt towers and gold-lined tea-room; and the Teradaya, an inn at which Sakamoto Ryōma was attacked and injured about a year before his assassination. Also of note is the Gokōgu shrine, which houses a stone used in the construction of Fushimi Castle. The water in the shrine is particularly famous and it is recorded as one of Japan's 100 best clear water spots. Kyoto, Japan.

Dinner tonight is picture perfect, taking inspiration from beautiful plates prepared by some of my favourite chefs... Although it may appear to be 'fancy', I'm here to tell you it's much simpler than that and possible for the untrained cook! On the menu tonight (between essay writing and exam studying) Asparagus wrapped in Balsamic and Garlic marinated Steak Rounds on a bed of Rosemary Cinnamon Mashed Potatoes, seasoned and embellished with Chili Flakes and Extra Balsamic Vinaigrette, Salt and Pepper. For the Steaks I simply dressed them in Vinaigrette and lightly dusted them with Curry Powder and laid them flat to prepare them for the Veggies. Next, add my chopped Garlic Cloves and Boiled Asparagus to each round and ROLL! Kebab skewers did the trick in holding them together until they finished in the oven (230 C for about 15 minutes - this will depend on your oven!). Remove your skewers, set your Mashies and begin to plate! 😍🐂🍴🍠🍅🍃🍂🌿 #athleattreats #foodpics #colourful #dinner #mealtime #getcreative #lovetoeat #lovetocook #loveforfood #alwayshungry #alwayseating #hitthespot #veggies #cinnamon #pictureperfect #student #toronto #fit #eatingright #cooking #flavourful #chili #spiceitup #mashies #steak #TheArtOfPlating #delicious #balanced #nutrition

Housing affordability measures coming 'very soon,' says Ontario's Wynne  BNN-TORONTO -- Ontario Premier Kathleen Wynne says her government will introduce a package of housing affordability measures "very soon" that she believes will have a swift impact on the hot Toronto-area housing market.  When asked if the package would include measures that may have a swift cooling effect on the market, such as a tax on foreign buyers or real estate speculators, Wynne says there's a need for action that will have an impact "fairly quickly." The premier wouldn't provide any details on the package, but says her Liberal government recognizes the complexity of the market and will be judicious in its approach.  Meanwhile, Ontario Progressive Conservative Leader Patrick Brown is calling for longer-term measures to address housing supply shortage. This fast, easy and delicious Asparagus Stuffed Chicken Breast recipe is a perfect meal for your weeknight dinner and it requires only 4-ingredient. . Ingredients: . 4 large chicken breasts 1 tbsp lemon zest salt and pepper 12 asparagus stalks, trimmed 3 slices mozzarella cheese 1 tsp garlic powder 1 tsp paprika 1 tbsp olive oil . Instructions: . Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. Cut the chicken breast in half, length-wise. Please do not cut all the way though. You need to create a pocket into each chicken breast. Season the inside of the chicken breast with lemon zest, salt and pepper. Place chicken on work surface and lay the mozzarella cheese and 3 asparagus inside of each chicken breast and fold over, enclosing the filling. In a small bowl mix together salt, pepper garlic powder and paprika. Then season the outside of the chicken breast with this spice mixture. Heat a large and oven safe skillet over medium-high heat. Add the olive oil. Cook the chicken for 3 to 5 minutes each side and until the chicken is golden brown on top. Place the chicken in the oven. Bake for 20 minutes. Make sure the chicken reaches the internal temperature of 165 degrees. . . . #feedfeed #cookinglight #toronto #torontofood #torontoeats #yahoofood #huffpostfood #foodgawker #food #buzzfeedfood #thefeedfeed #foodblogger #foodporn #cooking #foodie #food52 #torontoblogger #foodstagram #healthyeats #saveurmag #buzzfeast #instafood #recipe healthyrecipes #healthyeating #fbcigers

"There’s so many things about the world I want to change. I hate guns, I hate racism, I hate sexism, I hate homophobia, I hate prejudice, and I hate hate. These are all things I lay awake at night, wishing I could change. But if I had to narrow it down to one way I could personally change the world I would eradicate the term ‘slut’ and all its synonyms from every language. Growing up my sexuality was always something I was ashamed of and I did everything in my power to make sure no one ever felt the need to use the term ‘slut’ when referring to me. Although at times everything in my power was still not enough. I myself have even been a culprit of ‘slut’-shaming - belittling other women, based on actions or decisions that had nothing to do with me. I’m a product of a patriarchal society in which women are constantly being shamed for their sexuality and men are constantly commemorated for theirs. I am only now beginning to understand how truly wrong this is. No one deserves to be shamed based on their sexuality and how they chose to present it: privately with their partner or publicly to the world. I would like to change the world by removing the word ‘slut’ entirely so no woman ever has to feel hated because of her sexuality." • • • How would you like to #changetheworld? @bulldoghusein -  BCAA's  Among the most beneficial & effective supplements in any sports nutrition program are Branched Chain Amino Acids (BCAAs). These are the Essential Aminos of Leucine, Isoleucine, & Valine. These essential BCAAs are of special importance for athletes because they are metabolised in the muscle, rather than in the liver & make up one third of Muscle Protein. They play an important role in Protein Synthesis, Anabolism & Anti-Catabolism. Without adequate amounts of BCAAs muscle cells won’t heal as fast & they won’t grow. Most BCAA users report an immediate improvement in performance during extended periods of exercise, most likely due to better recovery potential. Consumed for several months, a diet high in BCAAs will reduce the incidence of infection by boosting immunity. You can also expect faster muscle growth during periods of intense training, & less muscle loss when attempting to lose weight. BCAA's are generally considered safe with little to no negative side effects. Overall, experts have agreed that consuming BCAAs can help stimulate protein synthesis, aid in glycogen resynthesis, delaying fatigue and help maintain mental function during intense exercise. Many scientists also consider BCAAs, especially leucine as the primary activator or muscle protein synthesis out of all the amino acids.  Be sure to check out our variety of BCAA's @bulldognutrition

Our last artist chat of the LAND exhibition! Featuring artists:  Shawntol Drakes @melanoiremedia, Alleben Purugganan @alleben, and Aimee Wu @aimeetwu  As part of an ongoing series, we invite Own the Walls' exhibiting artists & friends to participate in an intimate community discussion on their artwork and surrounding themes. . . *When: Thursday, April 13. Doors open 6PM, Discussion 7PM *Where: 4th floor, 215 Spadina Ave. *Kid-friendly - Free admission - Light snacks and drinks will be served* . . *Accessibility info*  215 Spadina Ave's front entrance is barrier-free and there is an elevator to the 4th floor. There are 2 gendered washrooms, and 1 gender-neutral wheelchair accessible washroom but no automated buttons. This is a dog-friendly shared workspace. Please avoid wearing scented materials. *If you require childcare or mobility assistance please let us know and we will strive to find a designated volunteer - contact ownthewalls.to@gmail.com  FEATURED ARTISTS:  Shawntol Drakes is an Afro-Guyanese mixed media artist from Toronto, ON. Her artwork focuses on showcasing the multi dimensional aspects of the experience of folks within the African Diaspora. Through photography, graphic design and writing, Shawntol tells stories of the multiplicities of the Black experience.  Alleben Tallo Purugganan is a community-based cultural worker and arts educator. She has previously worked on installations produced in collaboration with Filipino youth and caregivers as part of the Maleta Project in Gallery 44 and for Nuit Blanche in 2012.  Aimee Wu is a 21-year-old Chinese-Canadian creator. She loves to DIY and create works from unconventional mediums. Her art seeks to examine our personal attachments to the things around us, and the socio-spatial contexts to which the objects are transformed into iconographical symbols. Aimee is a proud owner of a golden retriever, and is an avid knitter. She is committed to further uncovering, uplifting and telling the stories oftentimes suppressed or forgotten.

"When I was approached to answer this question I truly didn't know how to answer the question. Thought about it, and thought about it some more. The only way I can change the world is by impacting good people in my life and hoping for a ripple effect one by one. I'm here to open up and say that I'm the individual many people told was never going to do anything in life. Never go to university, never graduate, never get a full time job, never know how to live on my own. Nothing but make bad choices. Each day in and day out I'm a living example that no matter what odds are against you that you are always in full control of your own future and no matter what life throws at you, you always have a choice to make, and that will determine what life and lifestyle you live. Life is determined by the short term decisions you make. We're only given one life and if I can speak to my friends and be the light for them at the end of the tunnel, then one day when another friend is down they can be their light and thus the ripple effect can begin.  So again to answer the question; "How would you like to change the world?" my answer is this: I wake up each day and simply be better then who I was the previous day. No bullshit, no shortcuts, no hand outs. If you want something in life and that specific thing can be different for everyone, lock in on it and don't stop until you've reached your goal and then when you have made it or reached your goal, spread your success with good people and show them there's always a way, even through tragedy. Thanks Michael GP for giving me the opportunity to open up to the world. ✌🏽" • • • How would you like to #changetheworld? Not in that youre a unique snowflake type of unique, but in the kind of beautiful unique that emerges when pressure creates a diamond or the turbulent sea polishes a pearl. It's a different type of beautiful unique that tests the depths of someone's insides and what pours from them is timeless wisdom, flexible compassion, endearing gratitude, and a calm understanding. These gifts, out in the world, are to everyone's benefit. How can you hate the teacher that taught you this? Don't curse your teacher, thank it.
